Question: What is the natural increase of the population of this country per year?

Answer: The natural increase of the population of this country per year is calculated by subtracting the death rate from the birth rate and multiplying the result by the current population. Independent clauses can also be joined by using a semicolon (;). Semi-colons are used less frequently than coordinating conjunctions, but they serve the same purpose. Compound-complex sentences contain one or more dependent clauses in addition to one or more independent clauses. Dependent clauses cannot stand alone as separate sentences.
Example (compound-complex): She likes to swim; last summer she swam every day.
